roles: Chairman of the Liberal Democratic Party caucus in the House of Councillors
supporting_quotes: Takemi was elected chairman of the Liberal Democratic Party caucus in the House of Councillors in November 2024, after Masakazu Sekiguchi resigned to become President of the House of Councillors.
Takemi used to be a professor of Tokai University whose main subject is international politics.

roles: Member of the High-level Panel on United Nations Systemwide Coherence
supporting_quotes: United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan appointed Takemi to a High-level Panel on United Nations Systemwide Coherence, which was set up to explore how the United Nations system could work more coherently and effectively across the world in the areas of development, humanitarian assistance and the environment.

events.canonical_org_name: High-Level Task Force for the International Conference on Population and Development
roles: Member of the High-Level Task Force for the International Conference on Population and Development
supporting_quotes: From 2012 to 2014, Takemi served on the High-Level Task Force for the International Conference on Population and Development, co-chaired by Joaquim Chissano and Tarja Halonen.

events.canonical_org_name: High-Level Commission on Health Employment and Economic Growth
roles: Member of the High-Level Commission on Health Employment and Economic Growth
supporting_quotes: In March 2016, Takemi was appointed by United Nations Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon to the High-Level Commission on Health Employment and Economic Growth, which was co-chaired by presidents François Hollande of France and Jacob Zuma of South Africa.

roles: WHO Goodwill Ambassador for Universal Health Coverage
supporting_quotes: In June 2019, World Health Organization (WHO) Director General Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus appointed Takemi as WHO Goodwill Ambassador for Universal Health Coverage.

roles: Member of the Commission for Universal Health
supporting_quotes: Since 2022, he has been a member of the Commission for Universal Health convened by Chatham House and co-chaired by Helen Clark and Jakaya Kikwete.
